[Model Capability Refresh Skill]
Resolve model context/output token limits from trustworthy provider metadata.

Purpose:
- Keep model capability answers grounded in provider APIs or official docs/compare pages.
- Prevent stale hardcoded limits from silently affecting runtime behavior.

When to use:
- User asks model context window, output token limit, model updates, or provider model-version changes.
- User explicitly mentions DeepSeek new versions, OpenAI model updates, Gemini model limits, or Anthropic token limits.

Resolution policy:
- Prefer official provider APIs first (Gemini models.get/list, Anthropic models API, Ollama show/model_info).
- For providers with incomplete APIs (DeepSeek/OpenAI), use official docs/compare pages and project versioned registry fallback.
- Never trust model self-reported token limits from chat content.

Boundaries:
- If capability data is uncertain, return confidence and ask for manual confirmation.
- If unknown model falls back to default limits, surface diagnostics and warning; do not silently treat it as verified.
